description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IM&amp;T Senior Purchasing Specialist – NHS, Bristol, £38,890 - £44,503 + excellent NHS benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bristol &amp; Weston Purchasing Consortium (BWPC) have an opportunity for a new Senior IM&amp;T Purchasing Specialist to join our busy, award-winning team. Based in Southmead Hospital we require an experienced individual to join our sourcing team, supporting a range of key projects sourcing goods and services, deriving strategic benefit and cost reduction for the clients it supports across the IM&amp;T Sourcing Category.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BWPC are proud to feature amongst our clients two of the largest NHS Acute Trusts in the UK. We support regional procurement activity, working to ensure our local health and welfare providers are able to deliver whole system cost reduction, whilst ensuring an optimised service delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt; As a Senior IM&amp;T Purchasing Specialist within the sourcing team, your primary activities will focus on the following:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Procurement strategy development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Procurement strategy execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supply base management:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder relationship management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;People management and leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOU:&lt;/strong&gt; The successful applicant will be able to demonstrate:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Circa 3 years’ experience of a procurement/contracting operating at a strategic level with evidence of applying Category Management principles,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record of realising sustainable financial savings and cost reduction together with evidence of leading procurements which result in tangible business change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical, numerical and problem solving skills – with the ability to both interpret and present outputs to influence key procurement strategy decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven negotiation and influencing skills, both with external supply base and internally with key client stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details, please access the Job Description and the Person Specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: Wednesday 11th November 2020. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Robert Walker&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Category Manager - IM&amp;T&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: robert.walker2@nbt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0117 4142666&lt;/p&gt;
